dismissalText.commentary: Ollie Pope lbw b Sajid Khan 3 (14b 0x4 0x6 17m) SR: 21.42

dismissalComment.html: Pope sweeps, hit on the front pad... given! He reviews instantly, but I'm not sure how confidently. Would have crashed into leg halfway up. Sajid gets his man for the third time in a row

dismissalText.commentary: Joe Root lbw b Sajid Khan 5 (6b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: ripping turn, Root is salmon! I was about to say the spin hadn't been excessive, but then Sajid rags one back from wide of off and completely flummoxes England's best player of spin. He was back in the crease, about at plumb as you could be as the ball rattled into his pads. Up went Chris Gaffaney's finger and Root won't bother to review, walks off with a resigned look on his face. Middle of middle, says ball-tracking
